-- MOVES-BNY Mellon Wealth hires Vivian Chan as wealth director in HK
-- By Luke Koshi in Bengaluru
-- Thu Dec 18, 2014 04:16AM EST
-- None



Dec 18 (Reuters) - BNY Mellon Wealth Management, a unit of Bank of New York Mellon Corp <BK.N>, has hired Vivian Chan as wealth director of business development in Hong Kong.

Chan will provide services to high net worth individuals and families, and will report to Chuck Long, head of greater China for BNY Mellon Wealth Management.